Post-Match Reflections: Devin Booker revealed how he could've been 'better' in the Suns blowout loss to the Kings, stating he should have trusted his teammates more and not forced plays.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phoenix Suns and Devin Booker dropped the second game of a back-to-back against the Sacramento Kings.
Booker scored 18 points on 6-for-16 shooting, with five assists, three rebounds, and two steals.
The Kings shot 64% from the field and 53% from three, leading to a blowout loss for the Suns.
The Suns flew from Utah to Sacramento late Tuesday night into the early hours of Wednesday, affecting their performance.
